# SIMD Optimization

## SIMD Module Structure
The project includes comprehensive SIMD optimization for vector operations:

- [src/simd/](mdc:src/simd/) - SIMD module with optimized operations
- [src/simd_vector.zig](mdc:src/simd_vector.zig) - SIMD vector utilities
- [src/simd/optimized_ops.zig](mdc:src/simd/optimized_ops.zig) - CPU-optimized operations
- [src/simd/enhanced_vector.zig](mdc:src/simd/enhanced_vector.zig) - Enhanced vector operations

## Key Features
- **Runtime CPU Detection**: Automatic detection of available SIMD features
- **Fallback Support**: Graceful fallback to scalar operations
- **Multiple Vector Types**: Support for different vector dimensions
- **Performance Monitoring**: Built-in performance tracking

## SIMD Operations

### Vector Operations
```zig
// Distance calculations
const distance = simd.euclideanDistance(vec1, vec2);
const similarity = simd.cosineSimilarity(vec1, vec2);

// Vector arithmetic
simd.addVectors(a, b, result);
simd.multiplyVectors(a, b, result);

// Normalization
simd.normalizeVector(vector);
```

### Performance Targets
- **Vector Operations**: 10x faster than scalar implementations
- **Distance Calculations**: 8x improvement in similarity search
- **Batch Processing**: 15x improvement in bulk operations
- **Memory Usage**: 40% reduction in memory overhead

## CPU Feature Detection
```zig
const features = simd.CpuFeatures.detect();
if (features.avx2) {
    // Use AVX2 optimized operations
} else if (features.sse4_1) {
    // Use SSE4.1 optimized operations
} else {
    // Fall back to scalar operations
}
```

## Best Practices
- Always check CPU features before using SIMD operations
- Provide fallback implementations for unsupported features
- Use appropriate vector sizes for optimal performance
- Profile SIMD operations to verify performance gains
- Handle alignment requirements for SIMD operations

